import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean Age: {data['age'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median Age: {data['age'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

data = pd.read_csv('lookup_people.csv')
chart = plot(data)
plt.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(gender_counts.index, gender_counts.values, color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Gender')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the gender distribution of the people in the dataset?')
    return plt

data = pd.read_csv('lookup_people.csv')
chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    education_levels = data['education_level'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(education_levels, labels=education_levels.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of education levels among the people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

data = pd.read_csv('lookup_people.csv')
chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x="income", data=data, ax=ax, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(data['income'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["income"].median():0.2f}')
    ax.axvline(data['income'].quantile(0.25), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Q1: {data["income"].quantile(0.25):0.2f}')
    ax.axvline(data['income'].quantile(0.75), color='orange', linestyle='--', label=f'Q3: {data["income"].quantile(0.75):0.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Income')
    ax.set_ylabel('Distribution')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of income levels among the people in the dataset?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
